ome security systems. Its entire business model revolves around pre-existing security systems. In essence, Alarm Relay allows you to switch providers or to use a security system that&#39;s been collecting dust. Alarm Relay does not manufacture or sell any equipment other than a control panel, and its monitoring offerings are limited. The company provides good customer service options.","This home alarm system offers fewer alerts than other companies in our home security review. Intrusion and power-failure alerts are included with the service plan, but you can add fire safety alerts for an additional fee. Alarm Relay is compatible with most alarm system equipment, but it requires you to already have the equipment before you can sign up for the monitoring service. It is disappointing that the company doesn&#39;t sell any equipment, but that is one of the major reasons its service is so affordable.","Alarm Relay&#39;s monitoring service covers the basics such as 24-hour monitoring, cellular connections, online account access, alarm history reports and follow-up notifications. These tools help the company offer a level of service similar to that of higher-ranked home security companies. When you begin service, you must pay a small activation fee and sign a one-year contract. The basic nature of this plan does not integrate a mobile app, home automation or two-way intercom capabilities.","Customer support representatives for Alarm Relay are available by email and phone. The support site also has a decent collection of tutorials and FAQs. The company does not offer installation services or live chat support. Since Alarm Relay does not sell equipment, you&#39;ll have to rely on the manufacturer warranty for each device in your security system."]},"id":"2c09a26c-0dd7-4666-87df-db0932dd3c84","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"330aa932-2f9b-4c53-88b8-11f40fbc6b06","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Alarm Relay bypasses the idea that a home security company needs to sell equipment. This allows the company to offer extremely affordable services. The monitoring services are extremely basic, but they can protect your home against the most common problems. If you already own a home security system, Alarm Relay deserves consideration. However, if you want advanced features such as a mobile app or home automation, then you may want to look elsewhere."]},"id":"b7af3c25-6453-4b59-817c-613fea390cc5","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_59770","url":"/alarm-relay-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"john-carlsen","url":"/author/john-carlsen","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"John Carlsen","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"jN6fuw55cS2xYQi25mfgkg","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-06-17T15:37:32Z","datePublished":"2014-06-17T15:37:32Z","name":"Alarm Relay","synopsis":"Editor's Note: This review has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it no longer ranks as a top 10 product. The original review is below, but check out our current top 10 about Home Security Systems here. Alarm Relay offers a low-cost approach to traditional home security systems.","review":{"rating":60,"verdict":"Alarm Relay has useful services and can keep your home secure for less money than any other company. ","pros":["Alarm Relay has the lowest monitoring fees in the industry."],"cons":["You must already own your security devices to use this service."]},"strapline":"Editor's Note: This review has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it no longer ranks as a top 10 product. The original review is below, but check out our current top 10 about Home Security Systems here. Alarm Relay offers a low-cost approach to traditional home security systems.","language":"en","dateModified":"2014-06-17T15:37:32Z","id":"uzLYYzhZSjYnNVNzuGuYad","meta":{"title":"Alarm Relay Review - Pros, Cons and Verdict","description":"Alarm Re